# Optional local overrides. Copy to `.env` in the repo root, next to the
# binary, or `%LOCALAPPDATA%\GridGlance\.env`.
# Existing process environment variables always win over file values.
#
# Packaged installers: a read-only URI is baked at release time from the
# GitHub Actions secret `GRIDGLANCE_MONGODB_READ_URI` — end users do not need
# this file for cloud track download. Use `.env` only to override that, or
# to unlock write/Track Scan.
#
# Never commit real credentials.

# Optional local override of the baked read URI (cloud track download).
# GRIDGLANCE_MONGODB_READ_URI=mongodb+srv://READ_USER:PASSWORD@cluster.example.net/?appName=GridGlance

# Read-write Atlas URI — unlocks Track Scan upload + shared settings write.
# If set alone, it is also used for reads (and overrides the baked read URI).
# GRIDGLANCE_MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://WRITE_USER:PASSWORD@cluster.example.net/?appName=GridGlance
